column5: Thinking of taking a drive up to Port Dover on Sun. Any word on the fishing would be greatful.  Thanks,  Mark
It's been slow at best but with warmer temps and SW winds they should be some moving around the end of the peir by sunday.
I heard today there were a few good ones being caught at the very end of the peir
Fished everywhere today from 9-1, no fish marked, no fish caught and nobody catching.

It was like that all over only a few being caught in the inner bay today and nothing in the outer bay the weather this week should get them moving in. That cold snap and wind storm made a mess of erie. There was tonnes of smelt out at bluffs dead and alive swimming around in big schools I think I will stick to burwell till bass opens.
